00:01:44,190 --> 00:01:45,120
Is he here to buy a horse?

19
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:46,680
Yeah.

20
00:01:47,550 --> 00:01:48,910
He's from a foreign country, though.

21
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:51,230
According to the Song Dynasty law,

22
00:01:51,230 --> 00:01:52,040
we are not allowed to sell a horse to a foreigner.

23
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:52,590
Someone's tailing you.

24
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:54,000
If you don't want to die, come with me.

25
00:01:54,950 --> 00:01:55,590
Mo'er.

26
00:01:58,440 --> 00:01:59,630
Do you want the horse or not?

27
00:02:03,270 --> 00:02:04,160
Buyou, this way.

28
00:02:04,190 --> 00:02:05,080
Quick, hurry.

29
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:13,910
Mo'er, go check if someone's behind us.

30
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:17,830
Did you see them?

31
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:18,800
No.

32
00:02:20,550 --> 00:02:21,750
Those two men were coming for you.

33
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:22,390
Did you see that?

34
00:02:22,630 --> 00:02:23,030
Yes.

35
00:02:23,030 --> 00:02:23,670
Now

36
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:25,830
only he and I can save you,

37
00:02:26,110 --> 00:02:26,910
you understand?

38
00:02:27,550 --> 00:02:28,550
What do you do then?

39
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:31,030
We're from the Kaifeng Court.

40
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:32,190
We arrest bad people.

41
00:02:33,270 --> 00:02:34,320
Are you from Thindu?

42
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,520
I'm from Samboja.

43
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:38,600
Geographically speaking, Samboja is right next to Thindu.

44
00:02:38,830 --> 00:02:39,670
That's right.

45
00:02:40,390 --> 00:02:42,630
Are you the Thinduese who made the Auspicious Sign?

46
00:02:43,670 --> 00:02:44,000
Yes.

47
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:46,240
Hey, listen.

48
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:46,960
Don't move.

49
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:47,960
Just speak with your mouth.

50
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,470
Are you the Thinduese who made the Auspicious Sign?

51
00:02:49,470 --> 00:02:49,830
Yes.

52
00:02:49,830 --> 00:02:50,320
All right.

53
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:51,320
It's him!

54
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:52,960
Come on, take a seat.

55
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:55,550
Don't be anxious.

56
00:02:56,470 --> 00:02:57,750
Just tell us

57
00:02:57,910 --> 00:02:59,670
what really happened.

58
00:03:00,190 --> 00:03:01,600
Take your time.

59
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:03,320
My grandpa is

60
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,600
(Thinduese name).

61
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:08,960
His name is

62
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:10,110
(Thinduese name).

63
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:12,110
So it's a name, all right.

64
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,360
He had a brother.

65
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:14,440
His brother was

66
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:15,830
(Thinduese name).

67
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:16,670
It's a name, too.

68
00:03:16,670 --> 00:03:17,270
I understand.

69
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:19,720
They had a few brothers.

70
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:22,670
But we didn't have enough food at that time.

71
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,030
Later,

72
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:26,670
a friend of him from Samboja...

73
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:27,750
I understand.

74
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:29,390
How about this.

75
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:31,160
Let's not start from your grandpa.

76
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:32,670
I want to know about you.

77
00:03:32,750 --> 00:03:34,800
How did you arrive in East Capital?

78
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:37,000
Six mouths ago,

79
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,190
those two merchants

80
00:03:38,550 --> 00:03:39,550
asked me to hide in the boat,

81
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:40,720
and brought

82
00:03:41,110 --> 00:03:42,830
me to the Capital.

83
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,270
I know how to light fireworks.

84
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,030
When I got here,

85
00:03:47,030 --> 00:03:50,320
I arranged shows everywhere.

86
00:03:51,110 --> 00:03:51,880
Later,

87
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:53,830
someone arrested me.

88
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:56,830
Why did they arrest you for lighting fireworks?

89
00:03:56,830 --> 00:03:58,240
They said I didn't have the documents.

90
00:03:58,520 --> 00:03:59,830
I was smuggled here.

91
00:04:00,550 --> 00:04:01,110
I see.

92
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,110
Where did they bring you?

93
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,030
The Office of Justice.

94
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:05,630
The Office of Justice?

95
00:04:05,630 --> 00:04:06,110
Yes.

96
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:07,600
What's next?

97
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,000
Later,

98
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,270
an officer

99
00:04:11,270 --> 00:04:13,910
brought me somewhere else,

100
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:16,600
a room in sheer darkness

101
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:17,640
inside a teahouse.

102
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,200
I couldn't see anything.

103
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:23,040
They forced me to make the Auspicious Sign.

104
00:04:23,270 --> 00:04:24,480
Can you tell me

105
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:26,920
how did the person look like

106
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,110
who made you do this?

107
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:31,480
I couldn't see anything!

108
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:35,390
But there was something special to his hand.

109
00:04:35,790 --> 00:04:37,720
Something special, how?

110
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:38,480
Where was it?

111
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,640
On his thumb.

112
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:40,790
His thumb was

113
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:42,480
carved with four characters.

114
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:43,790
What characters?

115
00:04:44,350 --> 00:04:45,390
What were the characters?

116
00:04:48,950 --> 00:04:50,640
It means

117
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:51,600
"A mind tranquil as still water."

118
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:53,390
"A mind tranquil as still water?"

119
00:04:53,390 --> 00:04:53,790
Yes.

120
00:04:54,510 --> 00:04:56,720
You said you were locked

121
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:58,000
in a room of sheer darkness.

122
00:04:58,110 --> 00:04:59,110
You couldn't see anything.

123
00:04:59,230 --> 00:05:00,720
How was it possible for you

124
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:02,350
to see the characters on his thumb ring?

125
00:05:02,550 --> 00:05:03,320
I remember

126
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:05,200
when he first asked me to make the Auspicious Sign,

127
00:05:05,510 --> 00:05:06,320
I refused to do it.

128
00:05:06,830 --> 00:05:07,270
Then

129
00:05:08,270 --> 00:05:09,160
he pointed his finger

130
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:10,600
at my forehead.

131
00:05:11,350 --> 00:05:12,160
Zhao Buyou.

132
00:05:12,350 --> 00:05:14,510
What's your job here at the Office of Justice?

133
00:05:16,760 --> 00:05:17,720
Copying books.

134
00:05:18,070 --> 00:05:20,320
Turns out you know that's your job.

135
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:22,200
Why bother solving cases then?

136
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,480
I understand.

137
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:34,350
At the Office of Justice.,

138
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:35,480
it's Di Lun.

139
00:05:39,230 --> 00:05:39,790
Mo'er.

140
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:40,830
Keep an eye on him

141
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:42,110
and send him to Kaifeng Court in a while.

142
00:05:42,390 --> 00:05:43,440
Brother, be careful.

143
00:05:43,550 --> 00:05:45,270
Shout out loud when you see a bad guy.

144
00:05:59,070 --> 00:05:59,720
Buyou.

145
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:00,670
Buyou.

146
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:01,270
Buyou.

147
00:06:01,270 --> 00:06:01,760
Mo'er.

148
00:06:01,950 --> 00:06:03,110
That man ran away.

149
00:06:04,230 --> 00:06:06,000
He heard we were about to bring him to the Kaifeng Court

150
00:06:06,270 --> 00:06:07,640
and said he was afraid of government officials.

151
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:08,760
I tried to stop him

152
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:09,950
but I failed.

153
00:06:12,670 --> 00:06:14,110
Did you see him?

154
00:06:14,270 --> 00:06:14,950
No.

155
00:06:15,550 --> 00:06:16,670
What should we do now?

156
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:19,350
That Thinduese is an important witness.

157
00:06:21,110 --> 00:06:22,350
We have to take our chance.

158
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:28,160
I can't wait anymore.

159
00:06:28,830 --> 00:06:29,480
Wen Yue.

160
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,320
Wen Yue.

161
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,950
Wen Yue.

162
00:06:32,950 --> 00:06:34,070
Buyou and Mo'er will be here soon.

163
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:34,830
Wen Yue.

164
00:06:35,790 --> 00:06:36,320
Mo'er.

165
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:37,670
A white horse?

166
00:06:39,070 --> 00:06:40,320
Where's Buyou?

167
00:06:40,350 --> 00:06:41,480
He said

168
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,270
he couldn't bear leaving you.

169
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,070
So he's not coming back.

170
00:06:45,350 --> 00:06:45,920
Oh right.

171
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:48,480
He also wrote a letter for you.

172
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,480
He bought that horse?

173
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:54,160
Right.

174
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:56,040
Buyou said you'd know when you saw it.

175
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:59,350
Why would Buyou buy a white horse for his wife?

176
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:12,160
Listen to me,

177
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,390
throughout the entire continent,

178
00:07:14,390 --> 00:07:16,320
and compared to the Han and Tang dynasties,

179
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:18,070
not even a single city

180
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:20,000
is as big as East Capital.

181
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,390
East Capital is just huge in size

182
00:07:22,670 --> 00:07:23,720
with numerous opportunities.

183
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:25,350
As long as you're a living person,

184
00:07:25,350 --> 00:07:26,390
you won't starve to death in this place.

185
00:07:26,950 --> 00:07:28,070
I guess

186
00:07:28,510 --> 00:07:29,640
you know what I mean, right?

187
00:07:31,830 --> 00:07:32,200
You...

188
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:32,790
I...

189
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:40,640
So this is where we part ways.

190
00:07:50,740 --> 00:07:51,300
[To my beloved wife]

191
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:54,380
[Divorce Letter]

192
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:00,160
I wish you can live a life of happiness.

193
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,950
A life of happiness, huh?

194
00:08:02,230 --> 00:08:03,320
That's very resolute.

195
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:04,600
This

196
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,720
doesn't look like what he will do.

197
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,640
What did you do with him

198
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:11,640
except buying the white horse?

199
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:12,760
Come over here.

200
00:08:13,270 --> 00:08:13,790
Ban'er.

201
00:08:16,550 --> 00:08:17,550
Where have you been?

202
00:08:17,550 --> 00:08:18,880
And what did Buyou say to you?

203
00:08:19,270 --> 00:08:21,350
He said, don't hesitate,

204
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:22,230
and leave the city right away.

205
00:08:24,790 --> 00:08:25,790
There's nothing else?

206
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:35,550
Zhao Buyou.

207
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:38,440
We expected you to come

208
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,590
work at the Kaifeng Court.

209
00:08:39,590 --> 00:08:40,320
But you didn't show up.

210
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:42,400
Why did you run off to this place?

211
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,350
Inspector Gu, Judge Wan, please sit.

212
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:47,440
I want to buy you some tea.

213
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:49,030
What's the matter?

214
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:50,670
Here's the thing.

215
00:08:52,880 --> 00:08:55,790
I lost my job a few days ago.

216
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:57,230
I was afraid my wife would find out.

217
00:08:57,590 --> 00:08:58,910
So I was anxious

218
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:00,590
to find a job at Kaifeng Court.

219
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:02,550
Let's just wait another day.

220
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:03,880
I'm not in a hurry now.

221
00:09:04,470 --> 00:09:06,030
That's not up to you.

222
00:09:08,910 --> 00:09:09,710
Continue.

223
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:12,110
I came here today...

224
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,640
Just tell us already.

225
00:09:19,470 --> 00:09:20,280
Inspector Gu.

226
00:09:22,590 --> 00:09:25,760
Back then when Bao Zheng resides at Kaifeng Court.

227
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:26,320
Wait a second.

228
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:28,350
Who's that again?

229
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,640
I said Bao Zheng.

230
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:32,200
Why did you bring that up?

231
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,280
When he was in charge,

232
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:42,470
Anyone could file a lawsuit in court.

233
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:44,000
All grievance must be avenged,

234
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:45,550
and all evil must be eliminated.

235
00:09:45,790 --> 00:09:47,470
May I ask, Inspector Gu,

236
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:50,880
can we do that in today's Kaifeng Mansion?

237
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:56,400
Zhao Buyou, listen carefully.

238
00:09:56,910 --> 00:09:58,760
Before we had Bao Zheng.

239
00:09:59,350 --> 00:10:01,590
Now we have Inspector Gu.

240
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:02,520
In East Capital,

241
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:05,470
everything is put under our control.

242
00:10:05,470 --> 00:10:06,470
We'll arrest every criminal.

243
00:10:09,110 --> 00:10:10,200
My investigation shows

244
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:13,110
Li Yan's case fifteen years ago

245
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:15,550
and the Auspicious Sign today

246
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:16,790
are the works of the same person.

247
00:10:17,910 --> 00:10:18,790
Do you dare to arrest him?

248
00:10:20,150 --> 00:10:20,880
Who's him?

249
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,520
The prosecutor,

250
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:24,000
Di Lun at the Office of Justice.

251
00:10:31,550 --> 00:10:32,200
Boss.

252
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:34,910
I knew something's off with this man.

253
00:10:36,110 --> 00:10:38,230
He's been hanging around since the trial opened.

254
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:41,880
Do you have evidence?

255
00:10:41,910 --> 00:10:42,440
I have.

256
00:10:45,590 --> 00:10:46,670
I am the witness.

257
00:10:47,670 --> 00:10:49,200
That doesn't count as evidence.

258
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:52,150
I can guarantee sure it's him.

259
00:10:52,670 --> 00:10:54,000
Your guarantee doesn't mean anything.

260
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:56,400
You can't prove that man's guilty.

261
00:10:56,790 --> 00:10:59,080
Zhao Buyou, I didn't know you were such a conspicuous man.

262
00:10:59,350 --> 00:11:01,470
You seriously want the Kaifeng Court to go against the Office of Justice?

263
00:11:01,470 --> 00:11:02,110
Is that correct?

264
00:11:02,550 --> 00:11:03,790
A few days ago,

265
00:11:03,910 --> 00:11:06,550
you were fired by Mr. Di.

266
00:11:07,350 --> 00:11:08,110
So

267
00:11:08,550 --> 00:11:10,030
you hold a grudge against him.

268
00:11:10,710 --> 00:11:12,710
You plan to pin this on him.

269
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:14,760
Am I correct?

270
00:11:25,710 --> 00:11:27,640
That's what happened.

271
00:11:27,710 --> 00:11:28,840
And then he just took off.

272
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:30,880
Try to give it another thought

273
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,280
and see if you have missed something.

274
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:33,670
Have I missed something?

275
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:35,200
Oh, right.

276
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:36,760
He wrote another letter.

277
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:39,200
He mentioned

278
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,230
an abandoned place in the eastern suburbs.

279
00:11:42,230 --> 00:11:43,150
I don't know what it is.

280
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:45,470
He seemed to arrange a meeting, but he wouldn't let me know.

281
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:47,960
The eastern suburbs.

282
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:50,200
Abandoned?

283
00:11:51,670 --> 00:11:52,760
Wen Yue, where are you going?

284
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:56,400
Mr. Zhao's getting a divorce!

285
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:58,320
- Wen Yue, you can ride a horse? - What are you doing?

286
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,110
I knew how to do it when you were still kids.

287
00:12:01,590 --> 00:12:03,320
Wen Yue, you are leaving?

288
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:04,760
Take care of my Father.

289
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:07,710
Yue!

